{{Infobox person | image = | image_size = | name = Anne-Marie Huby | caption = | birth_name = Anne-Marie Paule Monique Huby | birth_date = November 1966 | birth_place = Belgium | death_date = | death_place = | nationality = Belgian | residence = England | occupation = Co-founder and MD of [[Justgiving]] }}
'''Anne-Marie Paule Monique Huby''' (born November 1966) is a Belgian businesswoman, the co-founder, with [[Zarine Kharas]], of [[Justgiving]], a global online giving platform.
Huby started her career as a radio journalist in Belgium, before becoming head of the UK arm of the charity [[Médecins Sans Frontières]].<ref name=ParsiKhabar>{{cite news|last1=Davidson|first1=Andrew|title=Zarine Kharas Chief Executive of Justgiving|url=http://parsikhabar.net/individuals/zarine-kharas-chief-executive-of-justgiving/1892/|accessdate=17 June 2015|work=Parsi Khabar|date=14 October 2009}}</ref>
Huby and Kharas founded Justgiving in 2000.<ref name=Guardian>{{cite news|title=10 minutes with ... Anne-Marie Huby, co-founder of JustGiving|url=https://www.theguardian.com/women-in-leadership/women-leadership-blog/2014/oct/24/anne-marie-huby-interview-founder-justgiving|accessdate=17 June 2015|work=The Guardian|date=24 October 2014}}</ref>
