'''Ghana Union of Traders''' is the [[umbrella body]] that regulates the activities of trades in [[Ghana]]. The body also lobbies the [[Government of Ghana]] on issues that affect traders in the country.<ref name="guta">{{cite web | url=http://www.ghanatrade.gov.gh/Trade-News/businesses-welcome-new-ministry-of-business-development.html | title=Businesses welcome new Ministry of Business Development | publisher=Ghana Trade | accessdate=30 July 2017}}</ref><ref name="puls">{{cite web | url=http://www.pulse.com.gh/business/new-ministry-businesses-laud-nana-addo-for-creating-business-development-ministry-id6046911.html | title=Businesses laud Nana Addo for creating Business Development Ministry | date=13 January 2017 | accessdate=30 July 2017}}</ref>

