[[File:Rabbi Issamar Ginzberg.jpeg|thumb|Issamar Ginzberg]] '''Issamar Ginzberg''' is a [[business strategy]] and [[Marketing consultants|marketing consultant]].<ref name="RashtySandyJCGinzberg">{{cite web|last=Rashty|first=Sandy|title=Need marketing help? Ask the rabbi|url=http://www.thejc.com/business/business-features/115303/need-marketing-help-ask-rabbi|work=THE JEWISH CHRONICLE ONLINE|publisher=Jewish Cronicle|accessdate=25 March 2014}}</ref><ref name="JewishStandardGinzberg">{{cite web|last=Leichman|first=Abigail Klein|title=Chasidic marketing advice|url=http://jstandard.com/content/item/chasidic_marketing_advice/30257|work=New Jersey Rockland Jewish Standard|publisher=Jewish Standard|accessdate=24 March 2014}}</ref><ref name="YeshivaWorldNewsParnassah">{{cite web|last=Ginzberg|first=Issamar|title=Parnassah Expo Networking Tips from Rabbi Issamar Ginzberg|url=http://www.theyeshivaworld.com/news/headlines-breaking-stories/220142/-parnassah-expo-networking-tips-from-rabbi-issamar-ginzberg.html|work=Yeshiva World News|publisher=Yeshiva World News LLC|accessdate=24 March 2014}}</ref> He is the founder and [[CEO]] of Monetized Intellect Consulting, a business and marketing firm with offices in [[New York City]] and [[Jerusalem]]. Ginzberg also founded English Speaking Entrepreneurs Israel (ESEI), an organization that assists English-speaking businessmen in adjusting to the [[Israel]]i business market.<ref name="NerLeElefOutreachGinzberg">{{cite web|last=Ginzberg|first=Issamar|title=The Global Resource for Jewish Educators and Outreach Professionals|url=http://nleresources.com/2013/06/part-1-how-to-market-judaism/|work=Ner LeELef|publisher=NLE Resources|accessdate=24 March 2014}}</ref><ref name="HillelPorathESEI">{{cite web|last=Porath|first=Hillel|title=Join The English Speaking Entrepreneurs in Israel - ESEI LinkedIn Group|url=http://www.iyazam.com/english-speaking-entrepreneurs-israel.html|work=Iyazam|publisher=iyazam.com|accessdate=24 March 2014}}</ref><ref name