{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2015}} {{Infobox person | name = Kwee family | image = | image_size = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | death_cause = | residence = Singapore | nationality = Singapore | education = | occupation = Owners, [[Pontiac Land Group]] | salary = | spouse = | children = | parents = Henry Kwee | relatives = | website = http://www.pontiacland.com/ | restingplace = | religion = | alma mater = | networth = [[United States dollar|$5.3 billion]] (July 2017)<ref>{{cite web|title=Kwee family|url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/kwee/|website=Forbes|accessdate=17 July 2017|language=en}}</ref> }}
The Kwee family is a Singaporean family that owns the Pontiac Land Group, a privately held luxury real estate developer and hotel owner based in Singapore.<ref name=":0">{{cite web|title=Kwee family|url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/kwee/|website=Forbes|accessdate=17 July 2017|language=en}}</ref> The Kwee brothers Kwee Liong Keng, Kwee Liong Tek, Kwee Liong Seen and Kwee Liong Phing collectively run the group.
==Family overview== Henry Kwee Hian Liong, father of the Kwee brothers, was an Indonesian textile trader and real estate developer who emigrated to Singapore in 1958.<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":1">{{Cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/forbesasia/2013/11/20/next-tycoons-evan-kwees-passion-for-design/#f1d9821f1e46|title=Next Tycoons: Singaporean Evan Kwee's Passion For Design|last=Staff|first=Forbes|work=Forbes|access-date=2017-08-31|language=en}}</ref> He founded Kwee Inc. Pte Ltd in 1959 and the Pontiac Land Group (PLG) in 1961.<ref name=":2">{{Cite news|url=http://www.straitstimes.com/business/pontiac-land-makes-its-mark-in-us-with-style|title=Pontiac Land makes its mark in US with style|last=|first=|date=2015-05-13|work=The Straits Times|access-date=2017-08-31|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|language=en}}</ref> Henry Kwee passed away in 1988.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://eresources.nlb.gov.sg/newspapers/Digitised/Article/straitstimes19880419-1.2.60|title=CONDOLENCES|last=|first=|date=19 April 1988|work=|access-date=2017-08-31|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=}}</ref>
Kwee Liong Keng is the eldest of the Kwee brothers and serves as the managing director of PLG.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://sg.asiatatler.com/tatler-list/300list/kwee-liong-keng|title=Kwee Liong Keng|last=|first=|date=|work=Singapore Tatler|access-date=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=}}</ref> Kwee Liong Keng is married to Chua Lee Eng, from the Chua family that founded [[Cycle & Carriage|Cycle and Carriage]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://eresources.nlb.gov.sg/newspapers/Digitised/Article/straitstimes19710322-1.2.50|title=Marriage unites two wealthy families|access-date=2017-08-31}}</ref>He also served as Singapore's Non-Resident Ambassador to the Republic of Poland, among other public service positions.<ref>{{cite web|title=MFA Press Statement: Appointment of Singapore's Non-Resident Ambassador to the Republic of Poland|url=https://www.mfa.gov.sg/content/mfa/media_centre/press_room/pr/2009/200904/press_20090429_04.html|website=Ministry of Foreign Affairs}}</ref> Kwee Liong Tek is the chairman of the Group.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://sg.asiatatler.com/tatler-list/300list/kwee-liong-tek|title=Kwee Liong Tek|last=|first=|date=|website=Singapore Tatler|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref> Brothers Kwee Liong Seen and Kwee Liong Phing are both directors on the board.
The Kwee brothers via [[Pontiac Land Group]] own several luxury hotels in Singapore including Regent Singapore, [[The Ritz-Carlton Millenia Singapore|Ritz-Carlton Millenia]], the [[Conrad Centennial Singapore]], and The Capella Singapore, as well as office blocks and malls, such as Capitol Piazza, the [[Millenia Tower]] and the [[Centennial Tower (Singapore)|Centennial Tower]].<ref name=":0" /> PLG also developed and manage the [[Camden Medical Centre]].
In October 2013, the Kwee brothers agreed to provide $300 million in equity, supported by an $860 million loan from a consortium of Asian banks to enable the [[Tower Verre]] development in New York City. This is PLG's first major foray outside of Singapore amidst the tightening property market on the island state.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.straitstimes.com/business/pontiac-land-makes-its-mark-in-us-with-style|title=Pontiac Land makes its mark in US with style|last=migration|date=2015-05-13|work=The Straits Times|access-date=2017-07-17|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Singapore Billionaires Want A Piece Of The New York Sky|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/neerjajetley/2013/10/31/singapore-billionaires-want-a-piece-of-the-new-york-sky/#52fa23344c92|accessdate=1 September 2017|publisher=Forbes}}</ref> The Kwees are also redeveloping 2 of Sydney's historic sandstone buildings into a 240-room luxury hotel.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.businesstimes.com.sg/hub/property-2015/shaping-the-skyline-here-and-overseas|title=Shaping the skyline here and overseas|last=Rashiwala|first=Kalpana|work=The Business Times|access-date=2017-08-31|language=en}}</ref>
Third generation of Kwees are represented by Evan Kwee, son of Kwee Liong Tek and maternal grandson of [[George Aratani]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.legacy.com/obituaries/latimes/obituary.aspx?n=george-tetsuo-aratani&pid=163232202&fhid=10576|title=George Tetsuo ARATANI's Obituary on Los Angeles Times|website=Los Angeles Times|access-date=2017-08-31}}</ref> Evan Kwee is a director of Pontiac Land Group and the executive director of Capella Hotel Group Asia,<ref name=":1" /> and is married to Claudia Sondakh.<ref name=":1" /> His older sister Melissa Kwee is a social activist<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/global/2009/0316/048_lifes_calling.html|title=Life's Calling|last=Tan|first=Jessica|date=2009-03-06|work=Forbes|access-date=2017-08-31|language=en}}</ref> and chief executive officer of the National Volunteer & Philanthropy Centre in Singapore.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.todayonline.com/lifestyle/travel/jetsetting-nvpcs-ceo-melissa-kwee|title=Jetsetting with ... NVPC’s CEO Melissa Kwee|work=TODAYonline|access-date=2017-08-31|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://womanoftheyear.herworldplus.com/2007-melissa-kwee|title=2007 Melissa Kwee – Her World Woman of The Year|website=womanoftheyear.herworldplus.com|language=en-US|access-date=2017-08-31}}</ref> She is also a director on Pontiac Land Group.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.straitstimes.com/business/new-luxury-hotel-for-landmark-capitol-site-part-of-750m-redevelopment-project|title=New luxury hotel for landmark Capitol site, part of $750m redevelopment project|last=Teo|first=Esther|date=2013-04-30|work=The Straits Times|access-date=2017-08-31|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|language=en}}</ref> One of their cousins, Leland Kwee, is a director of Patina Hotels and Resorts, and investor.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/business/singapore-start-up-bemyguest-raises-total-of-s-11-5-million-9028334|title=Singapore start-up BeMyGuest raises total of S$11.5 million after Series A funding|work=Channel NewsAsia|access-date=2017-08-31|language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.breakingtravelnews.com/news/article/the-patina-thanburudhoo-brings-new-luxury-to-the-maldives/|title=The Patina, Thanburudhoo, brings new luxury to the Maldives|work=Breaking Travel News|access-date=2017-08-31}}</ref>
Kwee Liong Keng's daughters Kwee Wei Lin<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.themarthablog.com/2010/07/the-final-blog-from-singapore.html|title=The Final Blog From Singapore - The Martha Stewart Blog|website=www.themarthablog.com|language=en-US|access-date=2017-08-31}}</ref> and Kwee Su-Lin<ref name=":2" /> both hold senior positions at PLG.{{cn|date=April 2018}}
According to ''[[Forbes]]'', the Kwee family have a net worth of $5.3 billion, as of July 2017.<ref name=":0" /> The Kwee brothers reside in Singapore.<ref name=":0" /> The family support educational causes, arts and cultural causes, social causes and humanitarian causes.<ref>{{cite web|title=Liong Tek Kwee {{!}} Wealth-X|url=http://www.wealthx.com/articles/2015/liong-tek-kwee/|website=[[Wealth-X]]|date=23 October 2015}}</ref>
